Male palp (Fig. 29
A-D
): paracymbium well-developed, Va-I long and finger-like, Va-II strongly reduced (Fig. 29A, D). Distal process sturdy, strongly sclerotized and ending in a sharp tip (Fig. 29B, D). Terminal apophysis short and blunt (Fig. 29A, C). Tegular apophysis strongly sclerotized, triangular, with a rugose surface (Fig. 29A). Conductor distally twisted with a tiny, pointed process (Fig. 29A, 
C-D
).

Epigyne (Fig. 30
E-G
): darkish (Fig. 30E). Scape wide and squared with a translucent posterior margin (Fig. 30
F-G
). Spermathecae small, ovate, separated from each other by about 1.5 times their diameters (Fig. 30G). Fertilization ducts long and thin, reaching the spermathecae with approximately 2.5 loops (Fig. 30
F-G
). Copulatory ducts short and thick, slightly bent outward (Fig. 30
F-G
).
